provinces. By utilizing a stacked format, we can simultaneously compare total application volume per province alongside the internal risk composition. This allows the bank to identify 'risk clusters'—provinces where the proportion of 'High Risk' applicants is disproportionately high. Such insights are critical for tailoring regional lending policies and allocating credit officers to specific geographic hubs based on the localized risk profile.","visualType":"column","pageId":"2a158374-ecf9-4be7-b7a7-c439d6d0abc3","layout":{"x":12,"y":9,"width":9,"height":8},"queryRef":{"kind":"query","queryId":"2e5eab7c-b3af-4226-b541-9775d4d0b05e"},"visualOptions":{"multipleYAxes":{"base":{"id":"-1","label":"","columns":[],"yAxisMaximumValue":null,"yAxisMinimumValue":null,"yAxisScale":"linear","horizontalLines":[]},"additional":[],"showMultiplePanels":false},"seriesColors":{},"hideLegend":false,"legendLocation":"bottom","xColumnTitle":"","xColumn":null,"yColumns":null,"seriesColumns":null,"xAxisScale":"linear","verticalLine":"","crossFilterDisabled":false,"drillthroughDisabled":false,"forceAxisTicks":false,"crossFilter":[],"drillthrough":[]}},{"id":"b4a13362-ebbe-48f9-8fef-c4b3142431b2","title":"High-Risk Watchlist","description":"This high-risk exception report identifies applicants with critical vulnerability markers: a Debt-to-Income (DTI) ratio exceeding 50% and a Credit Score below 600. These individuals represent a high probability of default due to the combination of low creditworthiness and extreme financial leverage. This targeted list allows for manual underwriting intervention or immediate rejection to protect the bank's liquidity.","visualType":"table","pageId":"2a158374-ecf9-4be7-b7a7-c439d6d0abc3","layout":{"x":0,"y":9,"width":9,"height":8},"queryRef":{"kind":"query","queryId":"aa3cc89a-849b-4edd-9f50-1952868b4978"},"visualOptions":{"table__enableRenderLinks":true,"colorRulesDisabled":true,"crossFilterDisabled":false,"drillthroughDisabled":false,"crossFilter":[],"dril